HEADWORD: Split stitch
<hw>Split stitch</hw>. <def>A stitch used in stem work to produce a fine
line, much used in old church embroidery to work the hands and faces of
figures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

